President Trump met with several governors and members of Congress to discuss trade and agriculture. He emphasized the importance of fair trade deals and reducing trade barriers, particularly with China and the European Union. The President also mentioned ongoing negotiations to renegotiate NAFTA and expressed his desire to support American farmers. Secretary of Agriculture Sonny Perdue and U.S. Trade Representative Bob Lighthizer provided updates on trade initiatives, while Larry Kudlow, the Director of the National Economic Council, highlighted the positive impact of Trump's economic policies on growth and investment in the U.S. The President also mentioned progress in the trade dispute with China and the upcoming meeting with North Korean leader Kim Jong-un.